.TH ROM 3 "CMT" "ROM" "Memory Placement"

.SH NAME
ROM \- Place constants in read-only / program memory when possible

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #define INCL__ROM
.br
.B #include <CMT/CMT.H>

.SH FILES
CMT/KEYWORDS/ROM.H

.SH DESCRIPTION
Provides a macro that places variables into read-only memory or program
flash using the most appropriate mechanism for the target compiler and
architecture.

This allows constants, lookup tables, and static data to reside in
non-writable memory, conserving RAM and enforcing immutability.

.TP
.B ROM
Macro for declaring data objects in read-only or flash memory.

.SH USAGE
.nf
ROM int table[] = { 1, 2, 3, 4 };

ROM char message[] = "Hello";
.fi

.SH NOTES
- Intended for data objects, not functions.
- Runtime access semantics may differ between platforms.
- On AVR targets, PROGMEM data may require special access macros.

.SH SEE ALSO
.B CMT(3)

